he CRYSTALLINE WURMS...There are about 5 or six.  Work clockwise around the room.  Kill one, med in his spot - move UP to next one, kill him...move to his spot.  Just keep going around the room, it will drop. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=114739">Shokar's Stuff</a><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=114866">Catyra's Gear</a><br><img src="http://members.aol.com/shokaroffreeport/sword.jpg"><BR><A HREF="http://forums.delphiforums.com/newbiezone/start">Host of The Newbie(r) Zone Forum</A></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufalloraantrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falloraan Trueblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 10:32:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where is the Flame of Light spell?</span><hr size=1> There are only four Crystalline Wurms that spawn in that room. As for killing them, I recommend pulling them out the south entrance and fear kiting them. Have a snare/fear class with you. The wurms have a ton of HPs, so typically a stand-up fight is going to take a lot of mana/medding, and you will not maximize your time. Also, you are able to single pull the Crystalline Wurm out, even if you have the two wanderers in the passageway that goes to the Crystalline room. When you are pulling, on your way out just run way up the right side wall, so that you are running almost into the ceiling. Keep running along that path until you are forced to drop down, which should be just past the wanderers. Same strategy works in the main tunnel, with the glowing river running through it, when you have wanderers walking through there.  <p><CENTER><FONT COLOR="847bff"><B>Falloraan Trueblade<BR>52nd Season Half-Elf Cavalier<BR>Thunder Struck - Tholuxe Paells</FONT></B><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=38753" target="_Blank">Profile</A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucatyra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Catyra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 10:43:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/shokaroffreeport/counsel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where is the Flame of Light spell?</span><hr size=1> All four times I was in that cave we just walked in a circle and killed them all.  No one ever came even close to being in trouble. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=114739">Shokar's Stuff</a><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=114866">Catyra's Gear</a><br><img src="http://members.aol.com/shokaroffreeport/sword.jpg"><BR><A HREF="http://forums.delphiforums.com/newbiezone/start">Host of The Newbie(r) Zone Forum</A></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitchywhon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitchywhon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 11:02:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 